<item>
<title>[STO-1967] Ref Bug 140581: [BASF] RMAN 3.5.0: Memory exhaustion on AIX servers caused by RMAN Plugin 3.5.0</title>
<link>https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/browse/STO-1967</link>
<project id="18200" key="STO">StoreOnce</project>
<description><p>Raising this Jira with ref to Bug 140581 - <span class="error">&#91;BASF&#93;</span> RMAN 3.5.0: Memory exhaustion on AIX servers caused by RMAN Plugin 3.5.0</p> <p><a href="https://bugzilla.its.hpecorp.net:1181/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=140581" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">https://bugzilla.its.hpecorp.net:1181/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=140581</a></p> <p>Copying all details from bug for reference,</p> <p>SIE285919 - StoreOnce 5660 &#8211; Memory exhaustion on AIX servers caused by RMAN Plugin 3.5.0<br/> Customer Name: BASF SE (Germany)<br/> 5660: 4.3.9-2426.20 , RMAN Catalyst Plugin Ver 3.5.0 (new config)<br/> System Model: IBM,9105-22B , PowerPC_POWER10 , 64bit arch</p> <p>Problem Description: CU has two new AIX Servers installed in their environment and have installed the RMAN Catalyst Plugin Ver 3.5.0 around 45 days back.<br/> CU is facing frequent Memory spike related issues in the OS end.</p> <p>upon investigation from the Host OS end (IBM team), they identified that the Catalyst plugin executable file has been consuming more memory.<br/> Issue seen on both units and noticed since 20thNov.</p> <p>Involved IBM team and they pointed out this to Catalyst Plugin.<br/> This process is allocating 256 MB segment in heap memory. This points to potential memory leak. Please contact application dev / support to identify any known issues or troubleshoot for potential memory leak problem<br/> This process had already allocated 99 segments in heap memory "work text data BSS heap", max size of each segment is 256 MB . Some of segments were yet to assign/allocate page when system got dumped.</p> <p>PS: customer did remove “StoreOnceCatalystCopy –copy” from their backup script from our two AIX servers as workaround to have stable systems until source of the problem is identified, and we did stop rollout for remaining AIX servers.</p> <p>Request from dev team:<br/> CU suspecting that there is Memory LEAK for the Plugin and wants remediation.<br/> CU also has Linux hosts with the latest version and no issues observed on those hosts.</p> <p>Logs location:<br/> sftp://ei297945:X5bw$CY7ds*JT2iw@hprc-h1.it.hpe.com:2222/ <br/> (Screenshots, Catalyst plugin logs (INFO mode, Error Mode, and Extended Debug mode) have been collected and uploaded to FTP Site.)<br/> Local System: 10.189.83.35 (test1/test1) /home/test1/krishna/SIE285919_basf_rman</p> <p>As per plugin conf file we see below,<br/> optica1_logs:<br/> APPLICATION_MANAGED_COPIES:DISABLE<br/> CATALYST_PAYLOAD_CHECKSUM:DISABLE<br/> CATALYST_BODY_PAYLOAD_COMPRESSION:DISABLE</p> <p>aix:<br/> #APPLICATION_MANAGED_COPIES:ENABLE<br/> CATALYST_PAYLOAD_CHECKSUM:DISABLE<br/> CATALYST_BODY_PAYLOAD_COMPRESSION:DISABLE<br/> #CATALYST_TRANSFER_POLICY:LOWBANDWIDTH</p> <p>errors Reported:</p> <p>Description<br/> SOFTWARE PROGRAM ABNORMALLY TERMINATED<br/> Probable Causes<br/> SYSTEM RUNNING OUT OF PAGING SPACE<br/> Failure Causes<br/> INSUFFICIENT PAGING SPACE DEFINED FOR THE SYSTEM<br/> PROGRAM USING EXCESSIVE AMOUNT OF PAGING SPACE<br/> Recommended Actions<br/> DEFINE ADDITIONAL PAGING SPACE<br/> REDUCE PAGING SPACE REQUIREMENTS OF PROGRAM(S)<br/> &#8211;<br/> PROGRAM<br/> StoreOnceCatalystCopy<br/> USER'S PROCESS ID:<br/> 56361422<br/> PROGRAM'S PAGING SPACE USE IN 1KB BLOCKS<br/> 7998048</p> <p>Note: We have requested for more config details and waiting on response from customer.</p> <p>Update: 2024-12-11 09:20:21 UTC</p> <p>Raised few queries to customer on setup/configuration details and below are the response.</p> <ul class="alternate" type="square"> <li>Need to verify whether the backups are set up as application-managed copies or Catalyst-managed copies.<br/> --&gt; Catalyst managed, we have APPLICATION_MANAGED_COPIES:DISABLE in config</li> </ul> <p>• Is the Database in ARCHIVELOG mode for running online backups without shutting down/putting the DB in backup mode?<br/> --&gt; Yes, it is online backups, with ARCHIVELOG enabled</p> <p>• As it was mentioned earlier that the Catalystcopy will perform complete copy job, Is it possible, if you can perform / test the Catalyst copy operations within a reduced window, such as one week? <br/> This would help determine if the issue (memory exhaustion) can be reproduced under a lighter workload.<br/> --&gt; Customer will try to test this tomorrow</p> <p>--------</p> <p>2024-12-13 10:34:30 UTC<br/> Hi Sunny,</p> <p>Please find response from customer,</p> <p>1. Is this AIX server only for RMAN Plugin or there is any other application installed; If RMAN plugin is removed - is system working properly <br/> I’m not sure what is meant by this. Afaik the servers are solely used by oracle databases, but the system is working fine even if plugin is there/installed, the problem happens only when copy binary is started. If it is not running &gt; there is no memory leak &gt; hence all ok.</p> <p>2. Is there any difference between Linux RMAN system (which is working properly) and this AIX system in terms of configuration, installed application and workload</p> <p>Well, where to begin? I mean except different HW, architecture and OS? But the problem seems to be with just copy utility, because even if it is started “standalone” (not part of backup, so its not talking to rman or oracle) the leak appears</p> <p>-------</p> <p>2024-12-13 11:16:04 UTC<br/> Hi Sunny,</p> <p>CU has reverted with below details post performing the testing by running backups of shorter timeframe. (attaching detailed info which includes script details used by customer)</p> <p>About the test with shorten timespan, I think you are right guys, number of objects seems to be issue causing the leak. That would also explain why we didn’t notice it at very beginning with just one aix server in pilot.</p> <p>I tried with 1 week span, and I had to kill the process (at 9.17GB it was about filling the ram, I didn’t want to cause issues on server)<br/> /opt/catalyst_rman_plugin/bin/StoreOnceCatalystCopy --copy --filtermodifieddaterange <span class="error">&#91;03/12/2024-18:00:00&#93;</span>:<span class="error">&#91;10/12/2024-22:40:00&#93;</span></p> <p>Name PID CPU% PgSp Owner <br/> StoreOnc 47251940 9.1 4.52G root <br/> StoreOnc 47251940 21.4 9.17G root &lt;&lt;&lt; killed</p> <p>So I tried with just 2 days and this time cmd actually finished and it went “only” to ~3GB (I didn’t catch exact maximum allocation but it wasn’t much higher that 2,94)</p> <p>/opt/catalyst_rman_plugin/bin/StoreOnceCatalystCopy --copy --filtermodifieddaterange <span class="error">&#91;08/12/2024-18:00:00&#93;</span>:<span class="error">&#91;10/12/2024-22:40:00&#93;</span></p> <p>Name PID CPU% PgSp Owner <br/> StoreOnc 47251964 0.1 2.94G root</p> <p>root@aix9271250:/root#V8CMTAL1## --copy --filtermodifieddaterange <span class="error">&#91;08/12/2024-18:00:00&#93;</span>:<span class="error">&#91;10/12/2024-22:40:00&#93;</span> &lt;</p> <p>Operation Complete:<br/> Total number of Catalyst items queued : 0<br/> Total number of Catalyst items that failed to queue : 2032</p> <p>Thanks,<br/> Krishna.<br/> -------------</p> <p>2025-03-05 16:01:53 UTC<br/> Unable to reproduce this bug.</p> <p>Attempted to reproduce on AIX and Linux machines with more than 2000 objects (screenshot attached), but the object/files queued and copied successfully.</p> <p>------<br/> 2025-03-07 09:55:33 UTC</p> <p>Hi Sunny,</p> <p>What we have observed with customer environment is, </p> <p>when they run these for longer period (like weeks time) seeing issues but for 2days don't see any.</p> <p>updated dated with 2024-12-13 11:16:04 UTC has details captured by customer.</p> <p>If we can test for a week might help to reproduce this issue?</p> <p>Thanks,<br/> Krishna.</p></description>
