<comment id="5208294" author="JIRAUSER25702" created="Thu, 23 Oct 2025 01:23:58 -0700"><p>Hi <a href="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=srikrishna.pilli%40hpe.com" class="user-hover" rel="srikrishna.pilli@hpe.com">Srikrishna Pilli</a>,</p> <p>This new issue (customer: Sony - Japan) is different from the existing bug (this <a href="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/browse/STO-1967" title="Ref Bug 140581: [BASF] RMAN 3.5.0: Memory exhaustion on AIX servers caused by RMAN Plugin 3.5.0" class="issue-link" data-issue-key="STO-1967">STO-1967</a>, customer: BASF SE - Germany).<br/> Please create a separate bug report for the customer Sony - Japan.</p> <p> </p> <p>Difference are as follow - </p> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/secure/attachment/494291/494291_image-2025-10-23-13-53-09-301.png" height="274" width="825" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p></comment>
