<comment id="5206661" author="spilli" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2025 23:42:13 -0700"><p><a href="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rajiv.nagaraja%40hpe.com" class="user-hover" rel="rajiv.nagaraja@hpe.com">Rajiv Nagaraja</a><a href="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sshivam%40hpe.com" class="user-hover" rel="sshivam@hpe.com">Sunny Shivam</a></p> <p>Support received another customer (Sony Japan) which looks to be similar issue.</p> <p>Please find more details,</p> <p>StoreOnce Catalyst Plug-in for Oracle RMAN causes oracle instance crash.<br/> Sony Semiconductor Manufacturing Corporation (JP)</p> <p>HPE StoreOnce 3620 System 4.3.9-2426.20<br/> HPE StoreOnce Catalyst Plug-in for Oracle RMAN version 3.5.0(Latest)<br/> Microsoft Windows Server 2019 Standard(Build 10.0.17763.2803)<br/> Oracle Database 19c</p> <p>The instance of Oracle Database was crashed.<br/> Currently no issue, but the customer needs RCA.<br/> HPE OS support team has investigated this issue for analyzing heap dump of "oracle.ext".</p> <p><ins>They point out that libisvsupport_rman.dll in StoreOnce Catalyst plugin for Oracle RMAN cause this issue.</ins></p> <p>Log files </p> <ul class="alternate" type="square"> <li>SPLOIDB2 RMAN log</li> <li>collection_070439736Z.tar.bz2 StoreOnce support ticket</li> <li>TSS_SPLOIDB2_251009-151346_Log-SHA_support-all.zip Windows TSS??</li> <li>WER.zip heap dump(This includes 3 oracle.exe heap dumps)</li> </ul> <p>This issue has happen 3 times in the past.<br/> 1st 2023/03/24<br/> 2nd 2024/11/08<br/> 3rd 2025/09/08 00:21:52 (JST)</p> <p>OS event log(system):</p> <p>09/08/2025,00:21:52,Error,SPLOIDB2.oita2.sony.co.jp,7034,Service Control Manager,N/A,N/A,"The OracleServiceSPLCAL2 service terminated unexpectedly. This is the first time the service has forcibly terminated."<br/> 09/08/2025,00:22:48,Information,SPLOIDB2.oita2.sony.co.jp,7036,Service Control Manager,N/A,N/A,"The OracleServiceSPLCAL2 service entered the running state."</p> <p>Connector_OracleRMAN:</p> <p>2025-09-07 15:18:46.828081 (local 00:18): ERROR : 9844_9288 : RmanCommandManager.cpp : catalyst::plugins::rman::RmanCommandManager::updateBackupOptions : Ln 2000 : unknown error<br/> 2025-09-07 15:18:46.828081 (local 00:18): ERROR : 9844_12368 : RmanCommandManager.cpp : catalyst::plugins::rman::RmanCommandManager::updateBackupOptions : Ln 2000 : unknown error</p> <p>Here is the comment for OS support engineer.<br/> analysis file can be attached this thread after opening the case.<br/> ------------------------------------------<br/> While running the process "c:\app\oracle\product\19.0.0\dbhome_1\bin\ORACLE.EXE SPLCAL2", there was an attempt to free an invalid virtual address (0xc). <br/> This caused an exception (0xc0000374: STATUS_HEAP_CORRUPTION) and the process terminated with an error.</p> <p>The issue occurred at the address libisvsupport_rman+0xcced (0x0000018d`0b50cced), during the destructor call for a basic_string object, <br/> which tried to free a memory block at address 0xc. Since 0xc is not a valid address, a heap failure (FailureType = 0x9: heap_failure_invalid_argument) was detected.</p> <p>The process dump did not include the image file "libisvsupport_rman.dll", so we could not check the caller code. <br/> However, it appears that there is a problem with the handling of basic_string objects in libisvsupport_rman.dll.</p> <p>libisvsupport_rman.dll is likely a channel library allocated during Oracle Recovery Manager (RMAN) backup operations.</p></comment>
<comment id="5196309" author="JIRAUSER25011" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2025 05:07:32 -0700"><p>Hi Krishna,</p> <p>     Thanks for willingness to help. Will discuss with the engineer on this aspect. The latest is that we are not able to reproduce the issue on our local setup. Based on our experiments, one possible root cause is the network connectivity issue. Its tricky to get the system onto this state.</p> <p> </p> <p>Thanks and Regards,</p> <p>Rajiv</p></comment>
