<comment id="5117988" author="JIRAUSER25702" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2025 22:52:47 -0700"><p>Hi All,</p> <p>It appears that the issue is related to a network problem.</p> <p>From <b>Lab Experiment</b> -</p> <p>When the network is down for a certain duration—such as 40 seconds—memory usage continues to increase, but the memory is not released even after the network has recovered and stabilised.</p> <p><span class="image-wrap" style=""><img src="https://jira.storage.hpecorp.net/secure/attachment/483168/483168_image-2025-08-26-11-21-00-687.png" height="384" width="633" style="border: 0px solid black" /></span></p> <p> </p> <p>Additionally, traces of network issues are evident in the log files collected from the customer's environment.</p> <p> </p></comment>
