<customfieldname>Postmortem Questions</customfieldname>
<customfieldvalues>
<customfieldvalue><p> 1. What happened (describe key issues from initial customer call till resolution)? Include: release(s) involved, who was involved, engineering time spent.</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>2. What is the root cause? examples: Environmental, HW failure, SW bug, Process bug, Docs bug, .... (if root cause is not not known please provide information on what investigation are done so far)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>3. Could the variation of this root cause trigger other bugs? </p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>4. What additional tools or tool improvements would help during investigation or recovery of similar issues?</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>5. How long did it take to diagnose the root cause of the problem? (in man-hours for all dev/qa engineers involved)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>6. What was the customer impact?<br/> a) e.g. system down? disconnect? low performance? Please quantify the severity (how many hrs down, what performance the system was delivering etc.)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>7. What is the work around if any?</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>8. How likely is it to happen to other customers? (low, medium, high frequency is sufficient)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>9. What is the signature of the problem (list the panic string, if any, or other symptoms - e.g. media, fw errors, performance data, bios settings etc. that can reasonably precisely show the presence of<br/> the problem in case it happens again)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>10. What code/design changes would prevent this class of issues from happening?</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>11. What process changes would avoid the customer issue or customer escalation? For example: KB articles, Specification Reviews, Design Reviews, Code Reviews, Early testing, more testing, Documentation, Support, Marketing Materials?</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>12. Which of the following types of tests might have caught this problem? (e.g. unit test, functional QA test, system integration test, performance test)</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>13. What went well?</p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> <p>14. Have you linked all the dependent bugs and other issues using following links? <br/> i.Blocked by link type to link all bugs/issues that are “must fixes” in order to “fix” this case/escalation <br/> ii.Mitigated by link type to link all actions, other issues that are required to be taken to “mitigate” this class of problem/cases </p> <div class="panel" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;border-width: 1px;"><div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #CCFFCC;"> <p>Answer goes here</p> </div></div> </customfieldvalue>
